Listening to the cold, clamorous Cleveland-like clungles,
Within the bowels of the half-hearted, hard-headed hungles,

Read the following poem. Do all the last words of each line rhyme together?

In a secluded tidy sandy bay 
In the delightful month of May
My love and I spent a whole week.

Then came that very infamous day.
Of all times, it would come at the start of May.
That was when you suddenly passed away.
